00:00:12.820 --> 00:00:14.750
- [Narrator] Welcome
to the QCC Art Gallery

00:00:14.750 --> 00:00:16.830
at Queensborough Community College,

00:00:16.830 --> 00:00:19.470
a college of the City
University of New York.

00:00:19.470 --> 00:00:21.840
The QCC Art Gallery is celebrated as a

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:24.520
cultural beacon within
the Borough of Queens,

00:00:24.520 --> 00:00:26.630
for its world-class exhibitions,

00:00:26.630 --> 00:00:28.790
honored for its architectural beauty,

00:00:28.790 --> 00:00:30.670
critically acclaimed for its permanent

00:00:30.670 --> 00:00:33.260
collections and nationally
recognized for its

00:00:33.260 --> 00:00:35.110
creative learning experiences.

00:00:35.110 --> 00:00:37.280
The beautiful QCC Art Gallery,

00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:39.190
known some 50 years ago as the

00:00:39.190 --> 00:00:40.820
Oakland Golf Clubhouse,

00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:42.790
was awarded a Queensmark plaque by the

00:00:42.790 --> 00:00:45.450
Queens Historical Society for its stunning

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:48.300
renovation and historical significance.

00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:51.410
Since the gallery's renovation in 2004,

00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:52.930
its mission has been to host

00:00:52.930 --> 00:00:54.430
world class exhibits.

00:00:54.430 --> 00:00:56.930
Simultaneously serve as
a learning laboratory

00:00:56.930 --> 00:00:58.610
for Queensborough's own students,

00:00:58.610 --> 00:01:01.400
and host thousands of
student visitors from local

00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:04.150
elementary, middle, and high schools.

00:01:04.150 --> 00:01:06.810
Reflecting the full
range of ethnic diversity

00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:09.510
of both the college and
the Borough of Queens,

00:01:09.510 --> 00:01:11.180
known as the most diverse county

00:01:11.180 --> 00:01:12.700
in the United States,

00:01:12.700 --> 00:01:15.590
the gallery presents
quality exhibits and catalog

00:01:15.590 --> 00:01:18.670
publications of local,
national, international,

00:01:18.670 --> 00:01:20.780
and historical interests to broaden the

00:01:20.780 --> 00:01:23.041
appreciation and understanding of art,

00:01:23.041 --> 00:01:24.880
and art as interpreter.

00:01:24.880 --> 00:01:27.420
Several important
exhibits have been hosted.

00:01:27.420 --> 00:01:29.930
An American Odyssey, debating modernism,

00:01:29.930 --> 00:01:31.910
highlighted the works of some of America's

00:01:31.910 --> 00:01:34.750
most significant artists
such as Jackson Pollock,

00:01:34.750 --> 00:01:37.330
Jasper Johns and Frank Stella.

00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.170
The Andy Warhol Graphic
Works exhibit offer

00:01:40.170 --> 00:01:41.870
viewers a comprehensive review

00:01:41.870 --> 00:01:43.810
of Warhol's artistic development

00:01:43.810 --> 00:01:45.680
through the decades.

00:01:45.680 --> 00:01:48.610
The QCC Art Gallery's critically acclaimed

00:01:48.610 --> 00:01:51.400
permanent African art
collection represents the

00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:54.160
cultures of virtually
every country in Africa,

00:01:54.160 --> 00:01:56.230
through a remarkable collection of finely

00:01:56.230 --> 00:01:58.170
crafted statues and masks,

00:01:58.170 --> 00:02:02.100
exotically shaped tools
and delicate textiles.

00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:05.230
The vast permanent
collection of African masks

00:02:05.230 --> 00:02:07.720
seems to convey the hopes, dreams,

00:02:07.720 --> 00:02:10.830
and fears of people from
kingdoms and colonies

00:02:10.830 --> 00:02:12.330
throughout the continent.

00:02:12.330 --> 00:02:14.350
As a compliment to the
permanent African art

00:02:14.350 --> 00:02:17.780
collection the gallery's
fall 2007 exhibit,

00:02:17.780 --> 00:02:20.470
A Cameroon World, art
and artifacts from the

00:02:20.470 --> 00:02:22.560
Marshall and Caroline Mount collection,

00:02:22.560 --> 00:02:24.860
presented a rich and
fascinating collection

00:02:24.860 --> 00:02:26.440
of art and artifacts.

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:28.740
The most extensive Cameroon art exhibit

00:02:28.740 --> 00:02:31.763
in the United States
in more than 20 years.

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:35.250
The exhibit, Picasso Printmaker:

00:02:35.250 --> 00:02:37.110
A Perpetual Metamorphosis,

00:02:37.110 --> 00:02:39.700
from the Myra and Sandy
Kirchenbaum collection,

00:02:39.700 --> 00:02:41.930
launched in the spring of 2008.

00:02:41.930 --> 00:02:45.110
It featured many examples
of Picasso's prints

00:02:45.110 --> 00:02:46.900
that have never before been seen

00:02:46.900 --> 00:02:47.973
in a public gallery.

00:02:48.880 --> 00:02:51.350
The QCC Art Gallery is now planning the

00:02:51.350 --> 00:02:53.180
installation of its collection,

00:02:53.180 --> 00:02:55.730
the Jaime Andrade pre-Columbian art,

00:02:55.730 --> 00:02:57.780
as its second permanent exhibit.

00:02:57.780 --> 00:03:00.390
This fascinating collection
contains some of the

00:03:00.390 --> 00:03:03.280
oldest ceramic pieces
in the United States,

00:03:03.280 --> 00:03:05.870
many of which are 4000 years old.

00:03:05.870 --> 00:03:08.100
Among the precious items
in the collection is an

00:03:08.100 --> 00:03:11.010
ancient ceremonial throne from Ecuador,

00:03:11.010 --> 00:03:12.940
in the shape of a jaguar.

00:03:12.940 --> 00:03:15.720
Please visit us to
experience the rich, cultural

00:03:15.720 --> 00:03:17.930
treasure of the QCC Art Gallery,

00:03:17.930 --> 00:03:21.230
a world of art from the
past, present, and future

00:03:21.230 --> 00:03:23.370
that serves to enlighten and educate the

00:03:23.370 --> 00:03:25.213
community and beyond.

